studyDesigns.name: Study Design
studyDesigns.rationale: Protocol-defined study design for investigating efficacy and safety

arms.name: ABBV-951 Treatment Arm
arms.description: All subjects receive an oral loading dose of LD+DDCI followed by a 24-hour daily continuous subcutaneous infusion (CSCI) of ABBV-951. The dose is individualized and titrated during an Optimization Period to achieve optimal clinical response.

studyElements.name: ABBV-951 Treatment Arm - Screening Period
studyElements.description: Treatment period for ABBV-951 Treatment Arm during Screening Period

studyElements.name: ABBV-951 Treatment Arm - Optimization Period
studyElements.description: Treatment period for ABBV-951 Treatment Arm during Optimization Period

studyElements.name: ABBV-951 Treatment Arm - Maintenance Period
studyElements.description: Treatment period for ABBV-951 Treatment Arm during Maintenance Period

studyElements.name: ABBV-951 Treatment Arm - Follow-up
studyElements.description: Treatment period for ABBV-951 Treatment Arm during Follow-up

maskingRoles.text: This is an Open Label study with no masking

population.name: Study Population
population.description: Target population defined by eligibility criteria

objectives.name: Primary Safety and Tolerability Objective
objectives.text: To assess the local and systemic safety and tolerability of ABBV-951 delivered as a CSCI for 24 hours daily for up to 52 weeks.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of ABBV-951 as measured by patient-reported and rater-measured efficacy endpoints.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate PD symptoms via wearable device and biomarker research.

endpoints.name: Adverse Events
endpoints.text: Percentage of subjects with adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs) during the study

endpoints.name: Adverse Events of Special Interest
endpoints.text: Percentage of subjects with AEs of special interest (AESIs) during the study

endpoints.name: Infusion Site Evaluation Scale
endpoints.text: Percentage of subjects with numeric grade equal to or higher than 5 and percentage of subjects with letter grade equal to or higher than D on the Infusion Site Evaluation Scale at any time during the study

endpoints.name: Clinical Laboratory Test Data
endpoints.text: Change in clinical laboratory test data from Baseline to end of study

endpoints.name: Vital Sign Measurements
endpoints.text: Change in vital sign measurements from Baseline to end of study

endpoints.name: Electrocardiograms (ECGs)
endpoints.text: Change in electrocardiograms (ECGs) from Baseline to end of study

endpoints.name: PD Diary Off and On Times
endpoints.text: Average normalized daily "Off" time and "On" times as assessed by the PD Diary

endpoints.name: MDS-UPDRS Parts I-IV
endpoints.text: PD symptoms as assessed by the Movement Disorder Society-Unified Parkinson's Disease Rating Scale (MDS-UPDRS) Parts I-IV (or the UPDRS Parts I-V in countries where a validated translation of the MDS-UPDRS is not available)

endpoints.name: PDSS-2
endpoints.text: Sleep symptoms as assessed by the PD Sleep Scale-2 (PDSS-2)

endpoints.name: PDQ-39
endpoints.text: Quality of life as assessed by the PD Questionnaire-39 items (PDQ-39)

endpoints.name: EQ-5D-5L
endpoints.text: Health-related quality of life as assessed by the EuroQol 5-dimensions questionnaire (EQ-5D-5L)

endpoints.name: PKG Wearable Device
endpoints.text: PD symptoms (including tremor, bradykinesia, dyskinesia, daytime somnolence, and indication of propensity for impulsive behaviors) as assessed by the Parkinson's KinetiGraph™/Personal KinetiGraph™ (PKG) wearable device (as allowed by local regulations) from Baseline to the Week 26 Visit.

endpoints.name: Biomarker Research Endpoints
endpoints.text: Optional samples will be collected during the study to evaluate known and/or novel biomarkers related to PD, related conditions, ABBV-951, or drugs of a similar class.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) consists of all subjects who receive any ABBV-951 infusion and have a baseline and treatment observation for at least 1 efficacy outcome measure.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) consists of all subjects who receive any ABBV-951 infusion and have a baseline and treatment observation for at least 1 efficacy outcome measure.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received any ABBV-951 infusion AND has baseline observation AND has treatment observation for >= 1 efficacy outcome measure

analysisPopulations.name: Treatment Naive Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Treatment Naive Analysis Set (TNAS) consists of all subjects in the FAS who have the initial exposure to ABBV-951 in Study M15-741, i.e., subjects who had received ABBV-951 in another study prior to participating in Study M15-741 are excluded from the TNAS.
analysisPopulations.label: TNAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Treatment Naive Analysis Set (TNAS) consists of all subjects in the FAS who have the initial exposure to ABBV-951 in Study M15-741, i.e., subjects who had received ABBV-951 in another study prior to participating in Study M15-741 are excluded from the TNAS.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Included in FAS AND initial exposure to ABBV-951 occurred in Study M15-741 (no prior ABBV-951 in other studies)

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set consists of all subjects who receive any ABBV-951 infusion.
analysisPopulations.label: Safety
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set consists of all subjects who receive any ABBV-951 infusion.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed Consent Understanding
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject must be able to understand the nature of the study and have had the opportunity to have any questions answered by the investigator.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed Consent Signature
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject, if judged by the investigator to have decision making capacity, must voluntarily sign and date an informed consent form approved by an independent ethics committee (IEC)/institutional review board (IRB), prior to initiation of any study-specific procedures.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject must be an adult male or female, 30 years of age, or older.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Compliance
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject is willing and able to comply with procedures required in this protocol.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Vitamin B12 Levels
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have a low vitamin B12 level (< 200 pg/mL); or does not have low-normal vitamin B12 level (< 300 pg/mL) with elevated methylmalonic acid (MMA > 0.41 µmol/L) at Screening Visit 1 (V1).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Cognitive Function
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject has normal cognitive function (Mini-Mental State Examination [MMSE] score of 24 or greater). Subjects with mild cognitive impairment (MMSE score of 19 – 23 inclusive) may be enrolled if in the investigator's opinion, are able to adhere to all study requirements. Subjects with moderate or severe impairment (MMSE scores of 18 or below) may not be enrolled.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Investigator Suitability
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject is not considered by the investigator to be an unsuitable candidate to receive ABBV-951 for any reason.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Parkinson's Diagnosis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject must have a diagnosis of levodopa-responsive idiopathic PD.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Disease Activity and Medication
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject must meet the following disease activity criteria: Must be taking a regimen of oral medications for PD that has remained unchanged for at least 30 days before commencing ABBV-951; this regimen must include levodopa-containing formulations such as CD/LD IR, CD/LD-CR, CD/LD extended release, CD/LD/entacapone. Must have a recognizable/identifiable "Off" and "On" state (motor fluctuations) as established through investigator observation and confirmed by PD diary entries recorded during the concordance test performed during the Screening Period.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Off Time Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Must be judged to be inadequately controlled by current therapy in the opinion of the investigator and experience a minimum of 2.5 hours of "Off" time per day as assessed by PD Diary prior to Day 1 (V3). Subjects who have received DBS therapy are eligible for the study, provided they are considered stable, are still levodopa responsive, and meet all other eligibility criteria.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Skin Conditions Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have a history of significant skin conditions or disorders (e.g., psoriasis, atopic dermatitis) or evidence of recent sunburn, acne, scar tissue, tattoo, open wound, branding, or colorations that in the investigator's opinion would interfere with the infusion of study drug or could interfere with study assessments.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Substance Abuse Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have a recent (within 6 months prior to study drug administration) history of drug or alcohol abuse that could preclude adherence to the protocol in the opinion of the investigator.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Suicidal Ideation Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have significant current suicidal ideation within 1 year prior to study drug administration as evidenced by answering "yes" to questions 4 or 5 on the suicidal ideation portion of the Columbia-Suicide Severity Rating Scale (C-SSRS) completed at either screening visit, or any history of suicide attempts within the last 2 years.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Psychotic Episodes Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have a history or presence of psychotic episodes that in the investigator's judgment are not adequately controlled by second generation (atypical) antipsychotics and that could preclude adherence to the protocol.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Unstable Medical Conditions Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have other clinically significant unstable medical conditions or any other reason that the investigator determines would interfere with the subject's participation in this study or would make the subject an unsuitable candidate to receive study drug.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Allergic Reaction Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have a history of allergic reaction or significant sensitivity to levodopa or constituents of the study drug (and its excipients) and/or other products in the same class.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Levodopa Contraindications Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject does not have any known medical condition for which levodopa is contraindicated (e.g., suspicious undiagnosed melanoma, narrow-angle glaucoma, severe heart failure, severe cardiac arrhythmia, pheochromocytoma, untreated hyperthyroidism, or Cushing's syndrome and other circumstances where adrenergics are contraindicated).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Blood Donation Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject has not donated or lost 550 mL or more blood volume (including plasmapheresis) or received a transfusion of any blood product within 8 weeks prior to initial study drug administration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: COVID-19 Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject has no known active COVID-19 infection. Subject must not have signs/symptoms associated with COVID-19 infection or known exposure to a confirmed case of COVID-19 infection during 14 days prior to Screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pregnancy Test Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If female of childbearing potential, subject must have a negative serum pregnancy test at Screening Visit 1 (V1) and a negative urine pregnancy test on Day 1 (V3) prior to the start of the infusion of study drug.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Female Contraception
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If female, subject must be either postmenopausal, OR permanently surgically sterile OR for women of childbearing potential (WOCBP) practicing at least 1 protocol-specified method of birth control, that is effective from Day 1 (V3) through at least 30 days after the end of the infusion (end of Treatment Period).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Male Contraception
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If male and sexually active with female partner(s) of childbearing potential, subject must agree, from Day 1 (V3) through 30 days after the end of the infusion of study drug, to practice protocol-specified contraception.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pregnancy/Breastfeeding Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If female, subject is not pregnant, breastfeeding, or considering becoming pregnant or donating eggs during the study or within 30 days after the end of the infusion of study drug.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Male Procreation Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If male, subject is not considering fathering a child or donating sperm during the study or within 30 days after the end of the infusion of study drug (end of Treatment Period).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Investigational Product Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject has not received an investigational product other than ABBV-951 within a time period equal to 5 half-lives, if known, or within 6 weeks, whichever is longer, prior to study drug administration.

studyInterventions.name: ABBV-951
studyInterventions.description: Soluble formulation of carbidopa phosphate and levodopa phosphate (CDP/LDP) for continuous subcutaneous infusion (CSCI).

studyInterventions.name: LD+DDCI
studyInterventions.description: Oral loading dose of levodopa and DOPA decarboxylase inhibitor (e.g., Sinemet, Madopar) administered at treatment initiation.

studyInterventions.name: Oral LD+DDCI IR
studyInterventions.description: Immediate-release tablets (e.g., Sinemet 25/100) for rapid deterioration of motor symptoms or pump malfunction.

studyInterventions.name: Levodopa inhalation powder
studyInterventions.description: Inhaled levodopa (e.g., Inbrija) for serious medical need or pump malfunction.

studyInterventions.name: Non-ergolinic dopamine agonists
studyInterventions.description: Permitted medications such as pramipexole, ropinirole, or rotigotine.

studyInterventions.name: Selective MAO-B inhibitors
studyInterventions.description: Permitted medications such as rasagiline or selegiline.

studyInterventions.name: Apomorphine
studyInterventions.description: Must be washed out (30 days for CSCI, 12 hours for other forms) prior to ABBV-951.

studyInterventions.name: COMT inhibitors
studyInterventions.description: Must be washed out for at least 12 hours before initiation (e.g., entacapone, tolcapone, opicapone).

amendments.name: Amendment 7.0
amendments.summary: The purpose of this version is to correct minor clerical errors for consistency throughout the protocol and incorporate necessary protocol modifications due to the COVID-19 pandemic, as well as updating sample size estimation to approximately 240 subjects to accommodate participation of additional countries and account for higher-than-expected dropout rates.

commentAnnotations.text: The Screening Period may be extended up to a total of 90 days for extenuating circumstances, e.g., supply constraints.
The Monitoring Period can occur any time before V3, as long as it lasts for 6 consecutive days.
As allowed by local regulations, subjects will receive the PKG-watch following Screening Visit 1 (V1) and will be required to wear it during the Monitoring Period.
Software version 'DL.v01.05' is installed on the pumps.
Subjects enrolled under protocol v6.0 (or after) will use the Neria Guard infusion set at the start of enrollment.

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: A 52-Week, open-label, single-arm study to evaluate the safety and tolerability of 24-hour daily exposure of CSCI of ABBV-951

studyAmendmentImpacts.affectedSection: Section 7 - Statistical Methods & Determination of Sample Size
studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Sample size increased to approximately 240 subjects to accommodate more countries and higher dropout rates.

studyAmendmentImpacts.affectedSection: Section 4.3 - Loading Dose, Continuous Infusion Rates, Titration, and Extra Doses
studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Clarified F3 infusion rate reduction limits and medical necessity requirements.
Modified/added criteria to exclude subjects positive for COVID-19.

studyAmendmentImpacts.affectedSection: Section 5.8 - Study Drug and Study Devices
studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Added guidance on cannula length selection and infusion site rotation.
Changed reporting timeframe for product complaints to 24 hours.

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: Necessary protocol modifications due to the COVID-19 pandemic to minimize risk to subjects.
To provide further guidance to Investigators in the event of an infusion site reaction.
To mitigate the risk of muscle wall infiltration leading to pain and/or occlusion of the cannula.
To provide general guidance to investigators on possible causes of hallucinations/psychosis.
Correct minor clerical errors for consistency throughout the protocol.

studyChanges.summary: Updated sample size estimation to account for additional countries and higher-than-expected dropout rate.

studyChanges.afterText: F3 infusion rate may be reduced beyond the 20% limit... with approval from the AbbVie TA MD
studyChanges.summary: Clarified that F3 infusion rate reduction beyond 20% is permissible if medically necessary.
Added COVID-19 positivity as an exclusion criterion.
Changed the reporting timeframe for product complaints to 24 hours.
Removed references to caregivers throughout protocol and Operations Manual.
